  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening the Implementation and Expansion of Displacement Tracking Activities and Facilitating the Establishment of Humanitarian Hubs in North-Eastern Nigeria</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Through this project, IOM aims to continue to increase its emergency response capacity to better serve the humanitarian community in addressing the needs of the most vulnerable populations in North-East Nigeria. In order to do so, IOM&apos;s biometric registration expanded its target and included all affected population in the registration so the humanitarian community have been having more up-to-date data on the needs in the most-affected states of North-East Nigeria. Moreover, in order to expand the reach of life-saving activities that the humanitarian community is currently providing to the affected population, IOM is currently working on the establishment of the humanitarian hubs to provide support to the humanitarian community in order to address the short, mid and longer-term needs of IDPs and returnees of over 1 million affected people.</narrative>
  </description>
